Ex BBNaija’s housematehas advised artists to host a show where Permanent Voter Cards(PVCs) will be substituted for entry tickets. The approach, he said, will force youths to get PVCs. He tweeted: “Scenes where Naija artists come together and host free shows all over the country and the only gate fee is to show your PVC… another way we can push the “get your PVC agenda” “It’ll really work wonders in getting our message out there beyond SM, but then what do I know?”   I’ve been dreaming of DJ Cuppy- Lord Lamba     Tonto Dikeh and I are neither friends nor enemies – Uche…     ‘Who Wants To Be A Millionaire’ returns with Frank Edoho as…   Social media users reacted to the suggestion with different ways. - Advertisement - @savyrinu tweeted: “BBNaija celebrities can also organise meet and greet with PVCs. Think about it “ @imonocenforreal reacted: “Perfect strategy, if they can come together, organize a free show in local Government, Senatorial, State and National. Mode of entry will be PVC.. This strategy will change the political landscape. Let us reach out to them bcoz Nigeria belong to all of us.” @chiko4_naija said: “Nice concept may I remind you tht most nigerians only got their PVC as a means of identification many of them have never voted so if I may add to ur first idea that our celebrates should do a campaign on the importance of voting too.”